The paper discusses issues related to the evaluation of research papers using bibliometrics, which is a common topic in computer science research. Specifically, the paper highlights problems with the data and statistical analysis used in the Italian research assessment exercise, which could fall under several sub-categories such as digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and computer engineering (cs.CE).
